# Frontend Standards

## Color & Styling Tokens

Hex values live **only** in `client/src/theme/tokens.js`. Everywhere else use MUI theme tokens.

```jsx
// ❌ BAD
<Box sx={{ color: '#138DFB', padding: '16px', fontSize: '14px' }} />

// ✅ GOOD
<Box sx={{ color: 'primary.main', p: 2 }}>
  <Typography variant="body2">...</Typography>
</Box>
```

**Gradients** are defined in `tokens.js` and used via `sx`:
```jsx
import { gradients } from '../theme/tokens';
<Box sx={{ background: gradients.authBg }} />
```

## Spacing & Sizing

Always use MUI spacing scale — never hardcode px values.

```jsx
// ❌ BAD
sx={{ marginBottom: '24px', width: '240px' }}

// ✅ GOOD
sx={{ mb: 3 }}   // 3 × 8px = 24px
```

Sidebar width and other layout constants are defined once in `tokens.js`:
```jsx
import { layout } from '../theme/tokens';
sx={{ width: layout.sidebarWidth }}
```

## Typography

Always use MUI `variant` — never hardcode font sizes or weights.

```jsx
// ❌ BAD
<Box sx={{ fontSize: '24px', fontWeight: 700 }}>Surgeries</Box>

// ✅ GOOD
<Typography variant="h4">Surgeries</Typography>
```

## Reusable Components

Before building a new component, search `client/src/components/` for one that already exists.

```
GraftProgressBar   ← reused on Home, Surgeries list, Surgery Detail
StatusBadge        ← reused for ACTIVE / COMPLETED labels
PageHeader         ← reused for page title + action button rows
DataTable          ← reused for Surgeries, Technicians, Accounts lists
```
